summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganPrep skin and set makeup while supercharging your complexion with Morphe's Continuous Prep & Set Mist+. This micro-fine mist is amped up with ceramides to hydrate, nourish, and strengthen skin's barrier, electrolytes to enhance moisture for a healthy glow, and antioxidants for boosting elasticity.
details: DetailsBenefitsPreps skin, sets makeup & nourishes the complexionInfused with ceramides, electrolytes & antioxidantsNaturally radiant finishKey IngredientsCeramides, known to hydrate, nourish & strengthen the skin's barrierElectrolytes, known to enhance moistureAntioxidants, known for boosting elasticityResearch Results100% of users showed an immediate improvement in hydration*97% of users agreed makeup looked better and lasted longer*97% of users agreed skin felt nourished and hydrated with a healthy glow**Based on a 16-hour clinical study of 31 consumers.Item 2610861How To UseHold the bottle 8-10 inches away from face.Close eyes.Spray evenly after makeup application.IngredientsWater (Aqua, Eau), Panthenol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Rosa Canina (Rosehip) Fruit Extract, Panax Ginseng Root Extract, Glycyrrhiza Glabra (Licorice) Root Extract, Cucumis Sativus (Cucumber) Fruit Water, Enantia Chlorantha Bark Extract, Carica Papaya (Papaya) Fruit Extract, Rosa Centifolia (Rose) Flower Extract, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Extract, Ceramide NG, Oleanolic Acid, PPG-26-Buteth-26, PEG-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, PVP, Decyl Glucoside, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Isododecane, Glycerin, Propanediol, Butylene Glycol, Propylene Glycol, Citric Acid, Disodium EDTA, Magnesium Citrate, Potassium Citrate, Potassium Sorbate, Phenoxyethanol, Fragrance (Parfum), Benzyl Benzoate, Hydroxycitronellal, Linalool, Limonene, Hexyl Cinnamal.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsShipping Restrictions : This item cannot be shipped via air.

reviews.headline: A must for the summer! My pictures looked fabulous.
reviews.comments: If you have combination or oily skin & you plan on enjoying yourself at church, work function, party, reunion, etc. this setting spray is a MUST! I use this product to set my makeup and I haven't been disappointed yet. I can definitely tell when I have used it, along with a makeup primer & setting powder under my eyes, nose, & forehead.

reviews.comments: i love this setting spray. it sets my makeup and stays all day even in the hot midwestern summer. the problem is, everytime i buy one, the nozzle breaks off within a WEEK. yes you can pop it back on, but then it doesnt spray like it's supposed to. i really wish they would update their packaging because i do really love it.

reviews.headline: My New Favorite
reviews.comments: This is my new favrotie must have setting spray. It is very long lasting. I put it on to set my primer than in between layers and at the end. It is light and feels good on the skin. I have a very light makeup routine. I put this on at 9 in the morning with just concealer, blush, setting spray and powder and the blush and the blush and concealer are still on 12 hours later. If I do the full face with all of the products, my face still looks perfect over 12 hours later. It lasts just as long as the loreal one size dupe but without the hairspray smell and feel. This feels like it is good for your face and does not cause breakouts like other sprays have. It is a must have for everyday use.

reviews.headline: It's a no from me
reviews.comments: Always on the hunt for the perfect setting or prepping type sprays. Ive tried a lot. I used this one time and it made my makeup run down my face and my skin burned. My cheeks got super red, it was horrible. I thought it was a one off because I always moisturize the heck out of my skin and prep it well before applying makeup. I tried it again, same thing happened. Thankfully, I did not use as much as I had previously. I've used a $6 sett that worked wonders better than this one. I have learned my lesson. Sensitive skin beware.

reviews.headline: This is a fixing/activating/hydrating spray
reviews.comments:
Restocked during this spring sale - the fine molecule is awesome for absorbtion, ingredients are clean and smells fresh. 

From what I've learn and used, there is a difference between "setting" spray and "fixing" spray - which is why there is no alcohol in fixing sprays like this one (the active ingredient Alcohol Denat to actually dry and set the makeup), it is supposed to be used in between steps or for activating the make up underneath. 

Point being, I've been using this amazing spray for preping, during my make up,  and BEFORE setting spray like One size. Love it!

faceoff_positive.comments:
The Continuous Prep & Set Mist has quickly become an essential part of my daily beauty routine. This versatile spray delivers a refreshing burst of hydration while also ensuring that my makeup stays flawless all day long.

What sets this mist apart from others on the market is its continuous spray mechanism. The fine, continuous mist provides a lightweight and even application, evenly distributing the product across my face. It helps to create a smooth canvas for makeup application, ensuring that my foundation goes on seamlessly and lasts throughout the day.

One of the standout features of this prep and set mist is its hydrating properties. The formula is enriched with skin-loving ingredients, which work together to moisturize and nourish my skin. The mist feels incredibly refreshing upon application and instantly gives my complexion a healthy, dewy glow.

Another aspect that I appreciate about this mist is its versatility. Not only does it work wonders as a makeup setting spray, but it also serves as a great primer and can be used to refresh and revive makeup throughout the day. Its lightweight formula does not feel heavy or sticky on the skin, making it suitable for all skin types.

The packaging of the Continuous Prep & Set Mist is also worth mentioning. The sleek, compact bottle is perfect for travel and fits easily into my purse or makeup bag.

Overall, the Continuous Prep & Set Mist is a must-have for anyone looking to achieve a long-lasting, fresh-faced look. Its continuous spray mechanism, hydrating properties, and multi-purpose functionality make it an excellent addition to any beauty routine. I highly recommend giving this mist a try for a boost of hydration and makeup longevity.
faceoff_positive.headline: A Refreshing Essential: Continuous Prep & Set Mist Review

faceoff_negative.comments:
first- i received this item for free but this does not change my review at all. if i paid, i would probably have to get a different bottle because mine must be defective. but first, the pros: this makes my foundation go on very smoothly and it sets the face pretty nicely- when i hug people i don't leave a stain on their shirt now. if you like a dewy finish, it's very nice, but to me, a little tiny bit of translucent powder makes it perfect. however, it does burn your eyes so shut those tightly. i got it in my eyes once and they wouldn't stop burning- i had to wash off all of my makeup and was late for work. THE BIGGEST PROBLEM IS the bottle. the spray nozzle fell off like five times. sometimes it sticks on my finger and just pops off when i take my finger off. i just put the nozzle back on and give it a spray and it stays on until the inevitable next time it falls off. just now, the bottle fell off my shelf and the nozzle fell off. i picked it up and it's leaking everywhere, i think from the seal (the silver part between nozzle and bottle). AND THIS LEGITIMATELY SCARES ME!! i love my fingers and my face, i don't want this thing to explode and cause my fingers to get snapped off my hand or something. pressurized stuff is no joke, people! so just beware and don't let this fall off of your shelf. 

matter of fact, any pressurized product- shaving cream, dry shampoo, whipped cream- don't let the bottle get dented, cracked, etc. and if you start hearing hissing sounds, throw it far away and take cover!! heed this warning please!
faceoff_negative.headline: Good formula, beware of packaging!!! i said BEWARE
